        "description": "# pastel daemon\n\n[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/pastels/pastel-daemon.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/pastels/pastel-daemon) [![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/repos/github/pastels/pastel-daemon/badge.svg?branch=master)](https://coveralls.io/github/pastels/pastel-daemon?branch=master) [![Pypi](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pastel-music.svg?style=flat-square)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pastel-music) [![Pyversions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/pastel-music.svg?style=flat-square)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pastel-music)\n\npastel is a music library manager and server with a focus on metadata and\norganization. It provides a CLI and web interface for library management, the\nlatter of which communicates with the daemon. The daemon handles periodic tasks\nand reveals a GraphQL API for client requests.\n\nThe following audio codecs and containers are supported:\n\n- FLAC in FLAC container\n- MP3 in MP3 container\n- AAC in MP4 container\n- Vorbis in Ogg container\n- Opus in Ogg container\n\n## Getting Started\n\npastel can be installed via pip: `pip install pastel-music`.\n\nPython must be compiled with support for SQLite3, since pastel uses it as its\ndatabase system. pastel requires no dependencies not available in the python and\njavascript ecosystems.\n\nOnce installed, the database must be created. This can be done with the `pastel db create` command. Running that command will generate the database based on the\ndefined model schemas and bring you up to date with the latest migration.\n\n## Daemon\n\n### Webserver\n\n#### Authentication\n\n## Command-Line Interface\n\nA CLI is provided for management of the daemon and convenience. Some commands\nand functionality is present in both the web interface and the CLI, whereas\nothers are only present in one of the two. User and API key creation, for\nexample, are only present in the CLI.\n\n### Upgrading\n\nDatabase migrations are handled via the Flask-Migrate wrapper around alembic. If\nan update contains a database migration, run `pastel db upgrade` to run the\ndatabase migration.\n\n### Development\n\nDevelopment helper commands are included in the CLI but are not accessible by\ndefault. To make them accessible, set the `PASTEL_DEV` environment variable.\nThese commands allow for easy emptying of the database and insertion of test\ndata.\n\n\n",
